                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19099</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Manna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Antonio</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-07T21:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1916, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Two foreign consuls met me at the international border. I was informed by them
                    and by citizens that de la Rosa is still in Monterey enjoying full liberty and
                    has quite a following some of whom say they still intend to invade Texas
                    whenever opportunity affords.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
